        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1574481795" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16695513809327198250">We all know it.<br/><br/>They are out there, the hip ones, the rich ones, the drug addicts and the perverts.<br/>The young and not so young well tanned on high doses of alcohol and prescription and def. non-prescription drugs are just soooo bored - and boring. <br/><br/>Nevertheless, once again Bret Easton Ellis feels a calling to describe them all in detail.<br/><br/>Whereas American Psycho was a wake-up call, pointing at the utter restlessness of a twisted brain leading to - for lack of better words - nihilistic behavior in ext</span>
  <span id="freeText16695513809327198250" style="display:none">We all know it.<br /><br />They are out there, the hip ones, the rich ones, the drug addicts and the perverts.<br />The young and not so young well tanned on high doses of alcohol and prescription and def. non-prescription drugs are just soooo bored - and boring. <br /><br />Nevertheless, once again Bret Easton Ellis feels a calling to describe them all in detail.<br /><br />Whereas American Psycho was a wake-up call, pointing at the utter restlessness of a twisted brain leading to - for lack of better words - nihilistic behavior in extremis, The Informers is nothing but a "Let me see if I can drive this one to the bank".<br /><br />2 stars for the ability to put together full sentences.</span>
